    <Heading>
      What is Necko?
    </Heading>

    <BodyText>
    Necko is an extensible, scriptable API for client-side networking tasks built on XPCOM. It provides:
    </BodyText>

    <List>
     <ListItem> generic and extensible framework for fetching URLs </ListItem>
     <ListItem> async framework for pumping data to consumers (i.e., non-blocking i/o) </ListItem>
     <ListItem> generic cache service (LRU data store for mozilla) </ListItem>
     <ListItem> async DNS resolution </ListItem>
     <ListItem> implementations of common protocols (http, ftp, file, etc.) </ListItem>
    </List>

  </SlideBody>

